To integrate your app with Supabase, you need to run the following SQL script in your Supabase SQL Editor. This will create the necessary tables (`messages`, `art_gallery`, `hero_settings`) and set up the Row Level Security (RLS) policies so your app can read and write data.

### Supabase SQL Setup
Run this code in the **SQL Editor** tab of your Supabase dashboard:

```sql
-- 1. Create table for visitor messages
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS messages (
  id UUID DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() PRIMARY KEY,
  name TEXT NOT NULL,
  phone TEXT NOT NULL,
  content TEXT NOT NULL,
  timestamp TEXT NOT NULL,
  type TEXT NOT NULL -- 'Inquiry' or 'Direct'
);

-- 2. Create table for artwork gallery
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS art_gallery (
  id BIGINT GENERATED BY DEFAULT AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,
  url TEXT NOT NULL,
  title TEXT NOT NULL,
  description TEXT,
  comments JSONB DEFAULT '[]'::jsonb
);

-- 3. Create table for hero section images
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS hero_settings (
  id BIGINT GENERATED BY DEFAULT AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,
  url TEXT NOT NULL
);

-- 4. Enable Row Level Security (RLS)
ALTER TABLE messages ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE art_gallery ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE hero_settings ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

-- 5. Create Policies (Allowing operations used by the portfolio app)
-- Messages: Anyone can insert, read, and delete (managed by your admin logic)
CREATE POLICY "Public Messages Access" ON messages FOR ALL USING (true) WITH CHECK (true);

-- Art Gallery: Anyone can read, update (for comments), and delete (for admin)
CREATE POLICY "Public Gallery Access" ON art_gallery FOR ALL USING (true) WITH CHECK (true);

-- Hero Settings: Anyone can read, insert, and delete
CREATE POLICY "Public Hero Access" ON hero_settings FOR ALL USING (true) WITH CHECK (true);
```

I have also updated the `App.tsx` file to ensure the Supabase client is correctly initialized with the credentials you provided and that the data fetching logic is robust.

